about.summary: Pure Python read/write support for ESRI Shapefile format.

name: pyshp
raw_recipe:
{% set version = "1.2.10" %}

package:
    name: pyshp
    version: {{ version }}

source:
    fn: pyshp-{{ version }}.tar.gz
    url: https://github.com/GeospatialPython/pyshp/archive/{{ version }}.tar.gz
    sha256: 009e02b281d7f509c34d31aca3545334e45bea15136f3bb81a37b4d13e21f9bd

build:
    number: 0
    script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record record.txt

requirements:
    build:
        - python
        - setuptools
    run:
        - python

test:
    imports:
        - shapefile

about:
    home: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/pyshp
    license: MIT
    summary: 'Pure Python read/write support for ESRI Shapefile format.'

extra:
    recipe-maintainers:
        - pelson
        - ocefpaf
